Campus Energy Forecast  
Local Setup & Usage Instructions

This project contains a retro terminal-style login/register system with a Node.js + Express backend and MySQL database.

Important – Two Parts to Run
1. Frontend (HTML/CSS/JS) – the pages you see in the browser
2. Backend (server.js) – handles login/register and stores users in MySQL

Both must be running at the same time.

Prerequisites
• GitHub Codespaces (recommended) or local VS Code
• Node.js installed (version 18 or higher) – download from: https://nodejs.org
• npm (comes with Node.js)
• MySQL / MariaDB installed and running 
  (in GitHub Codespaces: already installed as MariaDB)
• VS Code extension: Live Server (by Ritwick Dey) – highly recommended

Step 1: Start the Backend (server.js)
The backend must run first – it listens on port 3000 and connects to MySQL.

1. Open terminal in Codespaces (bottom panel or press Ctrl + ` )
2. Go to the root folder (where server.js is located):

   cd /workspaces/Campus-Energy-forecast

3. Install dependencies (only needed once):

   npm install

   This installs: express, mysql2, bcryptjs, cors, body-parser

4. Start the server:

   node server.js

   You should see:

   MySQL connected successfully!
   Backend running → http://localhost:3000

   → Keep this terminal open – do not close it.

Step 2: Start the Frontend (pages in browser)

1. In VS Code Explorer sidebar → navigate inside the Login_page folder  
   (you should see index.html, register.html, css/, js/, etc.)

2. Right-click index.html → select Open with Live Server

   → Browser opens at something like:

   http://127.0.0.1:5500/Login_page/index.html

   or (in Codespaces):

   https://your-codespace-name-5500.app.github.dev/Login_page/index.html

3. You should now see the styled login page  
   (green text on black background, scan lines, green SIGN IN button, etc.)

Step 3: How to Test – What Username & Password to Use
There are no default users – you must register first.

Register a new user (recommended)

1. On the login page → click "Sign up" at the bottom

2. Fill in:
   • Username: choose anything (example: samridhi, testuser, energyfan123)
   • Password: at least 6 characters (example: test123, mypassword2025)
   • Confirm Password: same as above

3. Click REGISTER

4. You should see a green message:  
   "ACCOUNT CREATED SUCCESSFULLY! REDIRECTING..."

5. After ~2 seconds → automatically redirected back to the login page

Log in

1. Use the exact credentials you just registered:
   • Username: samridhi (or whatever you chose)
   • Password: test123 (or whatever you chose)

2. Click SIGN IN

3. Expected result:
   • Alert/message: "LOGIN SUCCESSFUL"
   • Redirect to dashboard.html (welcome screen)

Happy testing!

Any questions → check terminal output or browser console (press F12).
